                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.248/12–2445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-24T16:00:00+03:06"
                            >December 24, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 29—2:29 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>434. Re London’s 13407 to Dept December 22, repeated Jidda. British Minister told
                    me today that he has informed SAG that British concur in our requests re Dhahran
                    airfield and that with regard to Fifth Freedom British hope SAG will consult its
                    own national interests without regard to previous British objections now
                    withdrawn. No reply yet to us from SAG.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept 434; repeated Cairo for Giles as 293 and to London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
